And I'm telling you, I've seen a great escalation of war.

00:23:11.650 --> 00:23:15.480
So, it's just part of the end times.

00:23:15.480 --> 00:23:18.380
That's where we are, and Jesus is coming.

00:23:18.380 --> 00:23:19.818
So, are we ready to pray?

00:23:19.818 --> 00:23:21.902
Hey, did I have my communion?

00:23:29.470 --> 00:23:29.660
We went and got my communion crackers today.

00:23:45.245 --> 00:23:45.679
I went by and got them at the store up there, buddy.

00:23:45.679 --> 00:23:46.136
Yeah.

00:23:48.730 --> 00:23:49.020
My Welch's and my cracker.

00:23:49.020 --> 00:23:53.653
I don't want the whole bag, but I'll take some.

00:23:53.653 --> 00:24:00.320
See, I got my Welch's and I told Diana I don't want to do a chip again, but I got my little crackers.

00:24:02.613 --> 00:24:02.927
So, you can pray with me tonight.

00:24:16.560 --> 00:24:16.920
I told them, praise God, we got it.

00:24:16.920 --> 00:24:18.940
I like Welch's, too.

00:24:25.333 --> 00:24:25.462
It's a lot better than what is in those little cups.

00:24:25.462 --> 00:24:26.577
Father, we just thank you, Lord.

00:24:35.420 --> 00:24:35.635
We thank you, Lord, for your healing power that flows on the inside of us.

00:24:35.635 --> 00:24:38.073
We thank you, Lord, that by your stripes we're healed.

00:24:39.640 --> 00:24:43.480
And Lord, we just lift up this body before you.

00:24:48.766 --> 00:24:49.091
And we thank you, Lord.

00:24:49.091 --> 00:24:52.060
We give all the glory to Jesus.

00:24:52.060 --> 00:24:58.907
We thank you, Lord, for your fresh touch on Diana tonight, on Paisley, on Megan.

00:24:58.907 --> 00:25:02.834
Father, I saw the fire on my Megan tonight.

00:25:05.053 --> 00:25:05.520
I could see your eyes moving around.

00:25:05.520 --> 00:25:07.800
Father, I just believe that Megan is healed.

00:25:07.800 --> 00:25:14.855
And I thank you, Lord, the same power that raised Jesus Christ from the dead dwells on the inside of me.

00:25:14.855 --> 00:25:21.760
And I believe, Father, that today is our expiration date for the things that we need.

00:25:21.760 --> 00:25:30.133
Now, God, I pray for every single one of them tonight that the healing power of God flow through this camera.

00:25:32.780 --> 00:25:34.080
And we thank you, Lord, that by the stripes of Jesus, they are healed, too.

00:25:36.380 --> 00:25:42.447
And as I pray for them, we believe that the demonstrations and the manifestations of the glory are sent through this camera in Jesus' name.

00:25:53.480 --> 00:25:53.747
And we thank you, Lord, that we can take this body and it never loses its power.

00:25:53.747 --> 00:25:55.613
You know, it never gets old.

00:25:55.613 --> 00:25:56.994
It never expires.

00:25:56.994 --> 00:26:00.520
Galatians stands strong forever and ever and ever.

00:26:05.320 --> 00:26:05.888
The word of God is alive and it never loses its power.

00:26:05.888 --> 00:26:09.764
It's a pillar in your life.

00:26:10.618 --> 00:26:12.813
And we believe tonight that by the stripes of Jesus, we're healed.

00:26:14.120 --> 00:26:15.560
And he said he provided for us.

00:26:26.840 --> 00:26:28.583
And I believe that tonight the healing power of God flows from the top of their head to the soles of their feet.

00:26:28.583 --> 00:26:31.640
And we take this body in Jesus' name.

00:26:31.640 --> 00:26:34.695
Thank the Lord.

00:26:35.070 --> 00:26:37.726
I thank you, Father, for the blood.

00:26:37.726 --> 00:26:41.140
We denounce word curses, incantations, chants, voodoo, whatever it may be.

00:26:41.140 --> 00:26:43.307
Father, and we apply the blood of Jesus over my family tonight.

00:26:43.307 --> 00:26:45.610
We apply the blood over our health tonight.

00:26:51.034 --> 00:26:51.907
And we thank you, Lord, that the angels of the Lord are camping around and about this hotel room.

00:27:01.000 --> 00:27:01.800
And we thank you, Lord, that if there's anything you want to show us, Father, we plead the blood over my eyes.

00:27:01.800 --> 00:27:09.667
Father, I thank you, Lord, that I see only what you want me to see, I hear what you want me to hear.

00:27:11.800 --> 00:27:21.320
And as we enter into this time, Father, you show us that which is to come, for you said that you do nothing in the earth without revealing it to the prophetic voices first.

00:27:30.914 --> 00:27:33.086
So, Father, we believe that the healing power of God, the delivering power of God, you've come and you've set the captives free.

00:27:41.227 --> 00:27:45.900
And I believe for every single person here tonight, Father, to get a fresh touch from Jesus, that you become more real to them than even the very air they breathe, the very water they drink, the very food they partake of.

00:27:47.453 --> 00:27:58.213
I thank you, Father, that you become so real to them that they don't ever question in their mind whether Jesus loves them or not, that they are fully persuaded that what God has promised he's able also to perform it.

00:28:00.560 --> 00:28:07.715
And Father, we take the blood right now in the name of Jesus, and I thank you that if God be for me, who can be against me?

00:28:08.540 --> 00:28:14.635
I thank you, Father, that there is a covering over Diana, there's a covering over my Megan, over Paisley, and over Braden.

00:28:28.993 --> 00:28:29.225
I plead the blood of Jesus over our finances.

00:28:31.712 --> 00:28:36.453
And I thank you, Father, that you said in your word that there's some thirty, some sixty, and a hundredfold.

00:28:41.520 --> 00:28:42.693
And I believe we sow into good ground, and we don't sow into bad ground.

00:28:46.595 --> 00:28:46.790
We sow into the ground the Holy Spirit leads us to sow into.

00:28:46.790 --> 00:28:54.445
When he says, 'Give, and it shall be given unto us, good measure, pressed down, shaken together, and running over, will men give unto your bosom.

00:28:54.445 --> 00:28:59.160
' Father, I thank you that whatever we put our hands to will prosper, that we don't lack any good thing.

00:28:59.160 --> 00:29:04.691
Not one of us, every single one of us walk in abundance of blessing.

00:29:15.680 --> 00:29:16.160
We lack no good thing.

00:29:16.160 --> 00:29:17.120
Why?

00:29:30.571 --> 00:29:30.783
Because we have tither's rights.

00:29:30.783 --> 00:29:34.310
I'm a tither, and I believe you should be a tither.

00:29:34.310 --> 00:29:41.353
I believe with all my heart that God rebukes the devourer for my sake.

00:29:41.353 --> 00:29:46.560
That's what he said in his word, and I'm calling it in.

00:29:46.560 --> 00:29:50.467
People say, 'Well, Brandon, why are you believing for more?

00:29:50.467 --> 00:29:54.200
' Because it's going to take money to get the job done.

00:29:54.200 --> 00:30:03.674
It's like so many ministries are believing for so much, like Sister Billye's believing for stuff for her apartment thing in Israel for the people—it's Migdal is what it's called.

00:30:03.674 --> 00:30:05.760
There's so many people believing for stuff, you understand?

00:30:12.280 --> 00:30:16.520
And so I believe these projects, what the Holy Spirit's for the end times, for these Brush Harbor churches, for all the things that God has called us to do, is going to take money.

00:30:16.520 --> 00:30:21.500
So that's why I'm trying to teach you all how to latch on and believe God for more.

00:30:23.651 --> 00:30:24.560
It shouldn't just be your four and no more.

00:30:27.173 --> 00:30:32.833
It should be that we have enough money to get the gospel out and spread the good news throughout the whole world.

00:30:34.600 --> 00:30:49.020
And if you don't know how to believe that way because your church isn't teaching you, then I hope I can help you, because I believe in the power of seedtime and harvest, that whatsoever a man sows, that will he also reap.

00:30:49.020 --> 00:30:54.000
But if you don't, every seed produces after its own kind, and I just believe in that.

00:30:54.737 --> 00:30:55.884
And so I see so much lack.

00:31:07.151 --> 00:31:07.302
I see so many people believing for something.

00:31:07.756 --> 00:31:19.733
And as I was listening to them at this conference believing for, I mean, it was like mega money, like more money than is like, to me, the money that they need for this project, I thought, 'Lord, how do we get that?

00:31:19.733 --> 00:31:22.700
' It shouldn't be that the body of Christ is struggling for this.

00:31:22.700 --> 00:31:29.730
There should be a million surplus because we're doing what you asked us to do.

00:31:34.380 --> 00:31:34.770
Do you see what I'm saying?

00:31:34.770 --> 00:31:36.933
So, I was just thinking about that.

00:31:37.440 --> 00:31:47.640
And I know what the Lord has shown me about certain investments like cryptos and things, and I thought, 'Lord, we just need the fountain.

00:31:47.640 --> 00:31:51.520
We need that to turn on for this end-time harvest.

00:31:51.520 --> 00:31:56.080
' You know, because I know what he's shown me, but I know what he said to me about Satan.

00:31:56.080 --> 00:32:14.920
This is Satan's wheelhouse, and he always talks to me about finances and how the devil tries to block it from the believers, tries to keep people poor, because if he can control the money, he can control stuff.

00:32:14.920 --> 00:32:19.360
He tries to put his hand in there and block stuff.

00:32:26.766 --> 00:32:27.069
And that's why we come as a believing believer.

00:32:27.371 --> 00:32:33.265
And I told the Lord, 'There's seed in the ground.

00:32:33.265 --> 00:32:43.469
' I know there's people out there that have sacrificially given, you all, to churches, to ministries, and you haven't seen your harvest yet.

00:32:45.840 --> 00:32:47.600
So, I start going, 'Lord, what's the holdup?

00:32:47.600 --> 00:32:52.520
Teach me, Father, so I can teach all these people.

00:32:52.520 --> 00:32:55.360
What's the holdup to these people's prosperity?

00:32:55.360 --> 00:32:59.627
' Because some people say, 'Well, it's a lack of faith, brother.

00:33:10.222 --> 00:33:10.418
You know, it's like you're always praying for healing, you never get your healing.

00:33:10.418 --> 00:33:22.547
Well, you know, it's because you might be living in sin, you might—well, it could be because you haven't spoken right.

00:33:22.547 --> 00:33:31.679
' And there's always some kind of Christian cliché of why you haven't got your breakthrough.

00:33:31.679 --> 00:33:36.910
'Well, it's because you're in strife with your wife, that's probably it.

00:33:36.910 --> 00:33:44.480
' And I go, 'But what if you're not, and you're still doing all there else to do is stand?

00:33:44.480 --> 00:33:52.409
' But I believe in speaking and calling those things that be not as though they were, and calling that money in.

00:33:52.409 --> 00:34:01.544
But I got so tired because I was raised this way, always believing for the mailbox mentality.

00:34:01.544 --> 00:34:03.733
'Well, we need a miracle.

00:34:03.733 --> 00:34:14.223
Yep, Sister so-and-so, we didn't have money for food, so if Sister so-and-so doesn't give you the money, you don't have the money to get through the rest of the week.

00:34:14.223 --> 00:34:18.800
' But you live from miracle to miracle to miracle, but you don't live in overflow, but yet you sacrificially give.

00:34:27.190 --> 00:34:27.520
And I think, 'What is the holdup?

00:34:27.520 --> 00:34:29.406
Where is the break?

00:34:29.406 --> 00:34:30.520
' Where is this?

00:34:30.520 --> 00:34:38.250
So that's where I told Diana, oh, I got to take the blood.

00:34:44.412 --> 00:34:44.661
I apologize.

00:34:48.951 --> 00:34:49.133
I got on something because the Holy Spirit triggered me.

00:34:58.166 --> 00:35:02.320
I'm not going to lose this because this is going to help you.

00:35:02.320 --> 00:35:09.217
Father, I plead the blood of Jesus, and I apply the blood, and I thank you, Father, for the blood of Jesus right now.

00:35:19.045 --> 00:35:19.250
And we thank you, Lord, that it never loses its power.

00:35:19.250 --> 00:35:25.760
And I plead the blood of Jesus over this room, over me, my mind, my will, my emotions in Jesus' name.

00:35:41.920 --> 00:35:42.251
And we make much of the blood.

00:35:42.251 --> 00:35:43.577
Amen and amen.

00:35:43.577 --> 00:35:47.670
Now that's so much better than those little Dixie cup things.

00:35:47.670 --> 00:35:48.330
Okay.

00:35:48.330 --> 00:36:01.809
So I said I got so tired because I saw my mom and dad always sowing and struggling, and as a young man, I struggled myself when I first got married.

00:36:01.809 --> 00:36:07.745
We struggled really bad, and I got tired of it, living on food stamps, and you're sowing and you're giving.

00:36:07.745 --> 00:36:11.200
Like I said, we were required to tithe at our church.

00:36:22.025 --> 00:36:22.290
If we didn't tithe, we were fired.

00:36:27.420 --> 00:36:34.349
They would look at the register of who gave what, and if you were on staff and you didn't tithe a certain amount, they'd call you into the office and say, 'Where's the tithe?

00:36:34.349 --> 00:36:35.667
Where's your tithe at?

00:36:35.667 --> 00:36:37.920
' And I'd say, 'I didn't have it to give.

00:36:37.920 --> 00:36:39.320
We were trying to pay our electric.

00:36:39.320 --> 00:36:40.740
' 'Well, you know the rules.

00:36:55.770 --> 00:36:56.025
If you don't tithe, you don't work here.

00:36:56.025 --> 00:37:00.520
Either you tithe and you give, or you're fired.

00:37:00.520 --> 00:37:03.020
' So we were forced to tithe.

00:37:03.020 --> 00:37:04.684
That's just the way it was.

00:37:04.909 --> 00:37:06.260
You tithed before you paid your bills.

00:37:06.260 --> 00:37:14.120
And if you didn't, you were fired working on staff at this mega-church I worked at.

00:37:14.120 --> 00:37:17.737
And so I had a real hard problem with that.

00:37:31.927 --> 00:37:32.373
And my heart really was cranky about it because my kids weren't doing without—we were living on food stamps and I was angry.

00:37:38.420 --> 00:37:39.845
But one day I gave it to God, and I said, 'God, either it's true or it's not.

00:37:39.845 --> 00:37:44.743
Either you're a blesser or this whole thing's a lie.

00:37:55.740 --> 00:37:55.920
But I refuse to live this way anymore.

00:37:57.840 --> 00:38:03.640
You either anoint my mind—I know I'm a man that doesn't have a lot of education.

00:38:14.090 --> 00:38:14.320
I know my wife is a beautiful woman to me, and she's suffering.

00:38:14.550 --> 00:38:19.258
We had to go to thrift stores to buy our kids' clothes, all our baby clothes, all of it.

00:38:30.380 --> 00:38:30.670
We only looked for stuff at garage sales for a quarter, ten cents.

00:38:42.135 --> 00:38:42.350
What could we do to haggle to be able to clothe our kids?

00:38:56.547 --> 00:38:56.716
And that's the way it was forever.

00:38:56.716 --> 00:39:00.200
That's the way even our bottles, whatever we could find, we bought everything at garage sales.

00:39:00.200 --> 00:39:08.120
We would go to the rich neighborhoods and we would take 20 bucks, and we'd buy our kids' fall clothes with it, or summer, or whatever we had.

00:39:21.452 --> 00:39:21.696
And we were excited if we could get it at Target because their clothes were better than Walmart's.

00:39:22.672 --> 00:39:24.074
And so this is the way it was.

00:39:24.074 --> 00:39:27.000
And so that's what I was trying to tell people.

00:39:40.359 --> 00:39:46.804
I came up with the idea to do eBay—well, Diana did, it wasn't me.

00:39:49.987 --> 00:39:53.640
I was praying in the spirit, praying in the spirit, and then one day she came to me.

00:39:53.640 --> 00:39:57.667
She said, 'Brandon, I have an idea.

00:39:57.667 --> 00:40:02.800
' And I thought she was nuts because we didn't have enough money to pay our electric bill.

00:40:07.160 --> 00:40:08.338
And she said, 'Bren, I'm going to take this last $100 we have.

00:40:08.338 --> 00:40:15.460
We don't have enough to pay the electric anyway, so they're going to cut it off in two weeks.

00:40:29.714 --> 00:40:29.943
So let's just take that $100 and do something with it, and try to make it happen.

00:40:29.943 --> 00:40:32.716
' And I looked at her and said, 'Are you nuts?

00:40:33.391 --> 00:40:43.716
I can try to scrounge up $100 more to pay our electric bill, and we won't have any food money or gas money, but at least our power will be on so we don't go without power.

00:40:43.716 --> 00:40:47.488
' She said, 'No, I feel this in my spirit.

00:40:47.488 --> 00:40:49.994
' I said, 'Whatever you feel, hun, I'll back it.

00:40:49.994 --> 00:40:51.520
' So that's where it started from.

00:40:51.520 --> 00:41:01.336
But he got so tired of sowing in the offering and waiting for a miracle always, and instead he said, 'Whatever you do, I'll give you power to get wealth.

00:41:01.336 --> 00:41:04.663
You go out and make it happen, Captain.

00:41:04.663 --> 00:41:07.150
Stop waiting for a handout.

00:41:07.150 --> 00:41:12.247
' It's like this, you know, when people say, 'Teach a person to fish.

00:41:12.247 --> 00:41:16.440
If you give somebody a fish, they'll have enough for a day.

00:41:16.440 --> 00:41:23.720
If you teach a person to fish, they'll be able to feed themselves forever,' you know, kind of a deal.

00:41:25.564 --> 00:41:26.933
I probably butchered that, but it's similar.

00:41:33.405 --> 00:41:33.570
But I'm trying to tell you all, out of desperation, doing eBay, Poshmark, and Mercari changed our life.

00:41:35.893 --> 00:41:39.251
But we didn't wait for it to happen; we went out and took what's ours.

00:41:39.251 --> 00:41:41.865
We learned to go to thrift stores.

00:41:41.865 --> 00:41:42.840
It took us forever.

00:41:42.840 --> 00:41:48.131
Diana and me, praying in the spirit for hours and hours—that's where I learned to develop my gift.

00:41:48.131 --> 00:41:56.715
But it was out of desperation, and I would learn where to go, asking the Father, 'Show me where the good stuff is.

00:41:56.715 --> 00:42:00.528
I'm looking for something that sells for more.

00:42:00.528 --> 00:42:06.217
' So, just praying in the spirit, and eBay changed our life.

00:42:11.231 --> 00:42:11.476
The Holy Spirit used that to change our life.

00:42:20.431 --> 00:42:21.420
And it was to the point where, in the first six months, we made more money than we made an entire year at the church.

00:42:21.420 --> 00:42:22.870
And it started compounding.

00:42:22.870 --> 00:42:24.180
We just kept growing and kept doing it.

00:42:30.320 --> 00:42:30.580
But I want to tell you, I got so tired of the—wow, I wonder what that's all about.

00:42:33.150 --> 00:42:33.400
You hear those, please.

00:42:40.609 --> 00:42:40.867
I got so tired of the prosperity preaching at church.

00:42:46.058 --> 00:42:47.011
A lot of charismatic, 'Sow your $58 seed'—not that I'm knocking that, man—'Sow your 58 for your $58 miracle.

00:42:47.011 --> 00:42:49.630
' I'm very careful; I don't touch the anointing.

00:42:49.630 --> 00:42:55.560
But I got tired of hearing it and not seeing the fruit of it, and always not putting my boat into motion.

00:42:55.560 --> 00:42:59.040
And so I tell you all this because I think it gets real flaky there.

00:42:59.040 --> 00:43:03.869
There's a real flakiness to it.

00:43:03.869 --> 00:43:07.445
I asked God, 'Show me how to flip a car.

00:43:07.445 --> 00:43:12.406
' So I'd find a car that was on another part of town, try to find it for a cheap deal—800 bucks—and try to flip it.

00:43:12.406 --> 00:43:18.591
Put a little bit of money—it might be a clunker that's broken—put a little bit of money into it, clean it up real good, put some new tires on it.

00:43:18.591 --> 00:43:24.774
Maybe they're used, because I always look for used tires.

00:43:24.774 --> 00:43:30.716
You can find some tires that were not too treaded out.

00:43:30.716 --> 00:43:44.740
I don't know why I'm telling you, but there's some for somebody trying to figure out how to double and triple your money, asking the Holy Spirit to give you wisdom about it, do you know what I'm saying?

00:43:44.740 --> 00:43:47.874
Not waiting for somebody always to hand you a Holy Ghost handshake.

00:43:47.874 --> 00:43:49.265
'Here, brother, here's your $100.

00:43:49.265 --> 00:43:57.111
' You're going, 'Oh my God, thank God I got $100, that'll get me through two days.

00:43:57.111 --> 00:44:01.320
' And you're going, 'Oh God, I've got to believe for the next one.

00:44:01.320 --> 00:44:09.680
' But believing God for so much more than always just waiting for your Holy Ghost handshake at church.

00:44:19.040 --> 00:44:19.173
You know what I'm talking about—Holy Ghost handshake.

00:44:19.173 --> 00:44:22.453
You're looking for a sister with a lot of money.

00:44:26.880 --> 00:44:27.206
And a lot of times you see the ministry of hints.

00:44:27.206 --> 00:44:45.420
You're walking around going, 'Well, I'm believing God for my electric bill today,' and you're talking to the rich people at church, hoping they'll have sympathy on you, that they'll want to help pay your electric bill because you're going, 'Oh God, you know, we've been struggling.

00:44:45.420 --> 00:44:47.984
You know, we're believing God just like everybody.

00:44:47.984 --> 00:44:55.000
' And you look at them, they're going, 'Okay, well, I know what you're doing.

00:44:55.000 --> 00:44:57.849
You're asking for money in a polite Christianese way.

00:44:57.849 --> 00:45:01.587
' I didn't want to be that.

00:45:05.040 --> 00:45:06.608
I wanted to be the man with a picture in his hand.

00:45:06.608 --> 00:45:08.080
Teach me.

00:45:08.080 --> 00:45:10.577
Teach me to not fish with just a fishing pole.

00:45:10.577 --> 00:45:14.608
Teach me to fish with a net, Father.

00:45:14.608 --> 00:45:15.584
Teach me.

00:45:20.493 --> 00:45:25.600
And that's why I continually am asking the Father, and when I hear about Magdala and these projects—and I think it's like $20 million to finish this project, it's huge money, right?

00:45:34.880 --> 00:45:35.209
—and I go, 'That should not be.

00:45:35.209 --> 00:45:44.256
The body of Christ should be the head, not the tail, above and not beneath.

00:45:44.256 --> 00:45:57.707
' But I think a lot of the times because it is Satan's wheelhouse, and he tries to block the blessing from the body of Christ so much because he knows what it's going to take to get the gospel out, because why?

00:46:12.089 --> 00:46:12.258
It's all about souls.

00:46:17.248 --> 00:46:25.410
