01:04:48.764 --> 01:04:52.200
I don't want to learn from the young buck.

01:04:52.200 --> 01:04:55.760
I want to learn from the old one because they're still alive.

01:04:55.760 --> 01:05:08.040
It's the old deer with the old antlers that's made it through all the hunting seasons that you go, 'How did you make it?

01:05:08.040 --> 01:05:18.270
' The young buck, he's just dodged some arrows.

01:05:25.705 --> 01:05:26.030
He's dodged some bullets and he's still going, saying, 'I've made it.

01:05:26.030 --> 01:05:29.080
' And you're like, 'Sit down, buddy.

01:05:32.410 --> 01:05:32.675
You don't know nothing.

01:05:32.675 --> 01:05:43.140
' But it's the old deer that the meat's tough, and you go, 'How did you make it through all those hunting seasons?

01:05:43.140 --> 01:05:56.304
